# Random Password Generator (CLI)

A beginner-friendly Python command-line tool to generate secure, random passwords. Users can customize password length, number of passwords, and character types (letters, digits, symbols). The script handles invalid inputs and can generate multiple passwords at once.

## Features

- Generate one or multiple random passwords at a time.
- Customizable character sets: letters (a–z, A–Z), digits (0–9), symbols (!@#$%^&*, etc.).
- Input validation for password length, count, and character selection.
- Simple and interactive CLI interface.

## Installation

1. Make sure Python 3.x is installed on your system.
2. Clone the repository or download `password_cli.py`.

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
